"created_at":"2013-03-01t14:52:29z","updated_at":"2013-03-01t14:52:29z","body":"sure,\r\n1.) easy seperating the backup of oc stuff from user stuff\r\n2.) moving the user home to a separate mount point while keeping the database in the operating systems environment. this mount point can be in unix eg nfs and in windows eg a drive\r\n3.) user space will grow different than db space\r\n4.) when stuff needs to get changed, we can manage each point in its own way"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/14292998","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/2009#issuecomment-14292998","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/2009","id":14292998,"user":{"login":"deepdiver1975","id":1005065,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f67e101ad9531b7d25697b76e503e062e.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"bdba071ed68da9ce8edae53c364902ef","url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975","html_url":"https://github.com/deepdiver1975","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/deepdiver1975/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-01t14:59:00z","updated_at":"2013-03-01t15:01:32z","body":"during setup you already have the possibility to choose another location for your sqlite database.\r\nin addition there is a config parameter which allows you to change the log folder as well - should be documented in the config.sample.php.\r\n\r\nnothing to do here .......\r\n![images](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/1005065/209944/db04c91a-8280-11e2-99b5-22a330d27a36.jpg)\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/14293854","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/2009#issuecomment-14293854","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/2009","id":14293854,"user":{"login":"mmattel","id":3321281,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/2d576241f3ac901ec52f1ec4a9c3b77b?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f62fba4fe6711d41fdbfc7ccc04efb8f4.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"2d576241f3ac901ec52f1ec4a9c3b77b","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel","html_url":"https://github.com/mmattel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-01t15:16:10z","updated_at":"2013-03-01t15:16:10z","body":"hmmmm.\r\n\r\naccording to config.sample.php line 144, this is the datadirectory we both mention.\r\nwe can also see the entry in the config.php proper set up when the installation is done.\r\n\r\n- you can chose a different database type\r\n- you can chose a different location for the logfile (incl other log specific parameters)\r\n- you can set a particular data directory for the users home <and> the embedded sqlite db\r\n- but you can not separate the users home from the embedded sqlite instance\r\n\r\nso why closing this request? i really think that this is a good idea having the freedom by business needs to store things where it is best for. why do i have the restriction to use a separate external database when i want to store the users home somewhere else - this is the current impact. i just request a enhancement for more flexibility.\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/14298521","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/2009#issuecomment-14298521","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/2009","id":14298521,"user":{"login":"mmattel","id":3321281,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/2d576241f3ac901ec52f1ec4a9c3b77b?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f62fba4fe6711d41fdbfc7ccc04efb8f4.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"2d576241f3ac901ec52f1ec4a9c3b77b","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel","html_url":"https://github.com/mmattel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mmattel/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-01t16:42:24z","updated_at":"2013-03-01t16:42:24z","body":"@deepdiver1975 \r\n\r\nmay i do another math example:\r\n\r\nif you run oc under ubuntu in a vm, you may give this vm a total (virtual) disk space of 8gb\r\nletâ´s assume, that 50% is used by the os, means that 4gb is free of use.\r\nif you have (only) 20 users and you give each user a space limit of 500mb, which is not that much, and we assume a usage of 50%, you already need 5gb of space.\r\nthe database itself will by far not grow in that ways and if you reach values of these sizes you need a different database anyway. this means, that you should not put the users data into the vm but you can let the database there until it grows where you need to migrate it.\r\n\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/14299068","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/2009#issuecomment-14299068","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/2009","id":14299068,"user":{"login":"karlitschek","id":867445,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/87ce2b4531ee1a0c32b50e0d8f049224?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f06e7098636caebfc9c30c9f52eb905df.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"87ce2b4531ee1a0c32b50e0d8f049224","url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek","html_url":"https://github.com/karlitschek","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/karlitschek/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2013-03-01t16:53:28z","updated_at":"2013-03-01t16:53:28z","body":"in bigger scenarios you shouldn't use sqlite anyways but mysql or postgresql. so the data will be somewhere else anyways\r\n"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/comments/14309157","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/i